# Benefit App - Integrative Project 2024B 

This repository contains the code and resources for the Benefit App Project, conducted by our team at Afeka College.
Team members and roles: 
Gal Angel- Team leader /Team 
Yahav Ler- SCRUM Master /Team 
Yam Horin- QA Engineer/ Product Owner /Team 
Diana Gurvits- System Architect/ Technical Writer /Team 
Shaked Ben guy- DevOps /Team 
Yarden Krispel- DBA /Team 
Alon Bitran- UIX Engineer /Team 

The project was developed in agile method, thus the project divided into 4 sprints. In the end of each sprint 
we wrote a repotrt that containes the compleated tasks, difficulties, and unfinished tasks. 

*Project Overvie* 
The aim of the app is to give the user a platform for all the benefits he has from different cunsomer clubs or stores.
The project consists of a server-side component called "SuperApp" and a client application known as "MiniApp".
There are two clints in our program: A java clint, and an android client.
All the MiniApps designed for browsing and exploring points of interests.
The miniapp communicate with the SuperApp server to retrieve data from the database. 
 
 
 *Installation*
-Installation Instructions-

1. Visit the official DOCKER website: (https://www.docker.com/).

2. Choose the appropriate DOCKER version for your operating system. If you have macOs or linux, put your mouse cursore ov the doemlouad botton, and two
options for instaltion will showup. 

3. Open the the link from the downloads and install run the instaltion on your computer. 

4. Once the installation is complete, Docker should be ready to use.

5. Befor running the server of the program, make shure that the Docker is running on your computer.

-Accessing Database-

 You may access the databace through H2 console in the link: http://localhost:8085/h2-console .
 
-Insalling Workspace- 

1. Download Spring Tool Suite in the following link: (https://spring.io/tools/).

2. Select the appropriate version for your operating system (Windows, macOS, or Linux) and download the installer.

3. install Spring on your computer according your oprating system.
For Windows:

Run the downloaded .exe installer.
Follow the prompts to complete the installation.
You can choose the installation directory or go with the default one.
For macOS:

Open the downloaded .dmg file.
Drag the STS application to the Applications folder.
For Linux:

Extract the downloaded .tar.gz file to the desired directory.
Open a terminal and navigate to the STS directory.
Run the STS executable to start the IDE.

4. Launch Spring Tool Suite: after installation, launch STS from the Start menu (Windows), Applications folder (macOS), or terminal (Linux).
On the first run, select a workspace directory where your projects will be stored.


*Usage*

To use this project, clone the repository and navigate to the relevant directories for code, data, and documentation.

